gomodel:SYNGO_4570  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: SPAR2/SIPA1L2 is enriched in the PSD fraction of a PSD preparation from adult rat cerebellum (Figure 3d). It coimmunoprecipitates with ProSAP-interacting protein from the postsynaptic protein complex in rat cerebellar lysate (Figure 3e). Confocal imaging of dendrites from hippocampal neurons shows localization to postsynaptic spines (Figure 5c).. Experimental description: PSD preparation of adult rat cerebellum. Antibody against SIPA1L2 from rabbit and guinea pig were generated using the first 93 amino acids of rat SPAR2 expressed as glutathione-S- transferase (GST)-tagged fusion proteins in Escherichia coli BL21, purified, and used for generation of rabbit and guinea pig polyclonal antibodies.\n\nCo-immunoprecipitation of SPAR2 and ProSAPiP was performed from rat cerebellar lysates." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0575-6950" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1585-539X" ;
        dc:date           "2022-04-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4570" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

